<s>i reported this issue to bc last night.  like many of you, i am experiencing the exact same issue.   some of my older sites have the old captcha, but my new sites have re-captcha and the anti-bot module (is that the same as {module_ccsecurity} ?</s><s>), yet the spam seems equal across all sites.    i have some granfathered sites using wordpress, and none of those are experiencing this issue right now.   we have 60+ sites using bc.  most have this issue.  so i think it is a bc issue.  and they need to fix it.  i was quite disappointed that their response to me:   i have worked along with the engineering team and had a look on all sites to see the submissions.</s><s> it seems like the captcha isn't bypassed.</s><s> if the captcha was bypassed the submissions would've been on every second, or every 10 seconds.</s><s> so all the submissions that exists on the sites (the biggest number is ~500 on are hand made.</s><s> in order to overcome this, i would suggest to enforce captcha on your site and use the new captcha (because that one is harder to pass through).</s><s> this can be done from site settings -> captcha - http://screencasteu.worldsecuresystems.com/alex/2013-05-17_1053.png and then apply it to the form that is submitted.</s><s> if you still have issues please let me know and i will further assist you.</s><s> kind regards, alex   the bc response only looked at my older sites with the older captcha installed, when my request to them detailed examples across the board.  the mere existence of this forum thread should prove it isn't a site issue, but a bc issue.  i am in serious jeopardy of losing clients over this, so i hope bc takes this seriously.   everyone who has this issue needs to contact bc so they wake up and realize that they have a system problem.  or at least acknowledge it to us.  
</s></post>
</TEXT>
